# .clinerules — Claude Code Operational Rules
# These rules govern how Claude Code behaves in every session.
# They are non-negotiable and apply to all tasks on this project.

---

## SESSION BEHAVIOUR

- Read CLAUDE.md fully before starting any task
- Read BRIEF.md for the specific section relevant to the current task before writing code
- Ask one clarifying question maximum before starting — if the task is clear, start immediately
- Do not re-explain what you are about to do — just do it
- Do not summarise completed work in chat — write it to PROGRESS.md instead
- At the end of every session, update the Progress Log in CLAUDE.md and PROGRESS.md

---

## TASK DISCIPLINE

- Work on exactly one feature or component per session
- Do not refactor, rename, or reorganise files that are not part of the current task
- Do not add features that were not asked for
- Do not upgrade or change dependencies unless explicitly instructed
- If a task requires changing shared state or the data model, note it in PROGRESS.md before proceeding

---

## CODE QUALITY

- Always run the app after completing a task — check the browser and the console
- Fix all console errors before marking a task done
- Validate completed work against VALIDATION.md before ending the session
- Write the minimum code needed to complete the task — no over-engineering
- Keep components small and focused — one responsibility per file
- Do not use inline styles if a Tailwind utility class exists for it

---

## COPY AND CONTENT RULES

- Never alter, paraphrase, or simplify copy — use BRIEF.md as the source of truth
- If copy is needed for a component, read BRIEF.md first and copy it exactly
- Do not invent placeholder copy — if copy is not in BRIEF.md, ask before proceeding

---

## TOKEN CONSERVATION

- Keep responses short: code output + file paths only
- Do not explain code unless asked
- Do not repeat back the task description
- Reference files by path — do not paste file contents into chat
- Use /clear between tasks — never carry old conversation context into a new task
- Write decisions and notes to files, not chat

---

## FILE MANAGEMENT

- All new files go in the correct directory as defined in CLAUDE.md section 3
- Update PROGRESS.md at the end of every session with what was done and what is next
- If a bug is found that is out of scope for the current task, log it in CLAUDE.md section 11 and continue
- Do not delete files — comment out or deprecate instead

---

## WHAT NEVER TO DO

- Never add authentication, payments, dashboards, or AI features
- Never call external APIs (stub all CTAs with console.log for MVP)
- Never use dropdowns for survey answer options — always buttons
- Never show more than one question per screen
- Never allow the user to bypass the gate screen
- Never change the Q7 question text — it must include "just like this survey did"
- Never create a new session without reading CLAUDE.md first
